result.execSummary:
The defendant Joseph Bowie was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Controlled Substance [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).
  • Possession of Cocaine/Coca(2nd+) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

Employment condition will not apply if defendant is found unable to work through doctor excuse.

Defendant may not possess/consume any alcohol.

Defendant may not enter any bars/taverns.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

Defendant Joseph Bowie in court with attorney Gabriel G. Siehr.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 2:32 PM. State - here for FPT and there is a resolution. Plead G to #3, #6 & #7 remaining counts DRI. Probation of 3 years, all sentences with held and each count fine of $300 plus costs, conditions of probation: AODA, absolute sobriety, no possesion of alcohol, no entry into bars or taverns, FT employment, 200  hours community service. Siehr and Bowie agree. Court dismisses Counts #1, #2, #4 & #5. Bowie pleads G to Counts #3, #6 & #7 as alleged. Court has PLQ and goes over it with the defendant. Court finds the defendant is freely, voluntarily and intelligently entering his plea, waiving his constitutional rights and right to JT. Court finds factual baisis, accepts plea and adjudges guilty on each count. State makes final argument and asks to follow joint recommendation. Siehr makes final argument and asks to follow joint recommendation. Bowie makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: Count #3 - With hold sentence and place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: AODA and follow through with any recommendation, no consumption or possesson of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, obtain full time employment/schooling unless doctors excuse proving he is unable to work, 200 hours of community service to be completed within the first 18 months, fine of $300 plus costs. Count #6 - With hold sentence and place on probation for 3 years; $300 fine plus costs with same condtions as count 3, no additional community service hours. Count #7 - With hold sentence and place on probation for 3 years; $300 fine plus costs with same condtions as count 3 & 6, no additional community service hours. Apply bond posted, remainder to be paid through probation. Right to appeal, DNA with expunction rights, voting/firearms rights given.
Final pre-trial on April 27, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
Final pre-trial on April 27, 2016 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Joseph Bowie in court with attorney Gabriel G. Siehr.  Defendant Joseph Bowie in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 4:39 PM. Siehr and Bowie have complaint, waives further reading, willing to waive PH - no form filled out, went over that right verbally, would also like to address bond. Court does verbal collaquey, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State will be filing Information today that will mirror the complaint. Siehr waives formal reading of it as long as it mirrors the complaint, will proceed to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court explains to Attorney Siehr how this Court runs regarding FPT/ etc. Siehr - bond - asks for reduction in bond for stated reasons. State - bond - no objections. Court - bond - reduces to $1000.00 cash that has been posted, no consumption of alcohol.  Final pre-trial scheduled for April 27, 2016 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Joseph Bowie appears via video from FC jail with attorney John E Voorhees who appears telephonically with leave of the Court and is making a limited appearance today and states issue with finding counsel for the defendant (conflicts). Defendant had Sharon Gisselman originally and she is no longer willing to take the case.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 10:06 AM. Court sets for another AIA. Court informs Voorhees that the defendant appeared in Court on 2/22/16 and was advised of the charges and penalties and the current bond. Voorhees - bond - makes argument for lower cash bond for stated reasons. State - bond - objects to lower cash bond for stated reasons. Court - bond - continues bond at this point.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for March 7, 2016 at 11:00 am.
